reviews.text:
Worse mango sticky rice I've had. Mango bingsu also not nice. ice is tasteless. Mango ice cream so meh.

Only thing nice is Thai milk.tea.

Shifted into the area for about 1.5years and thought to give this place a try.

Saw it was offering some cooked food and I ordered the Fried chicken rice(I can't recall)

Presentation of food looked presentable. Portion was decent and the ingredients were pretty much bite size. Lettuce was fresh, 1 boiled egg(would be better if they are Ajitama eggs) and chicken was tender but batter has a little smell. Possibly the oil that was used to fry the chicken, was reused a few times. It will be nicer to have mango salad in the dish.

I enjoyed their Thai Milk Tea which I appreciated that it can be customised in terms of the sweetness.

Total damage : $9

Looks empty when we arrived. There was only another table. But.... Grab orders keep coming in. Delivery riders keep coming in to collect orders. So dun be deceived that no one comes here to eat. Place was staffed by 4 Thai ladies. For a while, felt like we were in Thailand. Bingsu not bad.

For some reason, their pizza and toasts is the most Delicious I have ever eaten.
Love the milk tea and bing soo too

Update 2023: oh my mango has rice bowl now! I like the chicken but not the rice (too soft), egg is not runny.

Is a very nice place for nice bingsu atmosphere is nice but please be patient with the order as there is some nasty people can't wait as I see there is order from platform too so please be patient with good food need patience don't just throw temper ðŸ˜‰
